Introduction

Kwon Eunbin (also known simply as Eunbin) is a South Korean actress and singer under Cube Entertainment. She is a former member of the girl group CLC. She was added to CLC after appearing on Mnet's survival show "Produce 101".

In January 2016, Eunbin became a contestant on the survival show Produce 101, where she represented Cube Entertainment. She was eliminated in episode 10 after ranking 35th place.

On February 23, Cube Entertainment announced that Eunbin, alongside Elkie, would be joining CLC as the group's newest member. She made her official debut as a member of the group on February 29 with the mini album 'REFRESH'. However, she was unable to participate in the album's promotions due to her participation in Produce 101.

In February 2022, it was announced that Eunbin would be playing a major role in TVING’s upcoming original sci-fi thriller, After School War Activities, based on the webtoon of the same name.
